20 Sec. 44. Section 86-2,103, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
21 amended to read:
22 86-2,103 (1) A district court may issue a warrant or other order for
23 the installation of a mobile tracking device, and such order may
24 authorize the use of that device within the jurisdiction of the court and
25 outside that jurisdiction if the device is installed in that
26 jurisdiction.
27 (2) For purposes of this section, mobile tracking device means any:
28 (a) Electronic an electronic or mechanical device which permits the
29 tracking of the movement of a person or object; or .
30 (b) Software program installed on a person's electronic device which
31 permits the tracking of the movement of a person or object.
